list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: a stand, booth, or compartment for the sale of goods in a market or large covered area.
an individual compartment for an animal in a stable or barn, enclosed on three sides.
a fixed seat in the choir or chancel of a church, more or less enclosed at the back and sides and often canopied, typically reserved for a particular member of the clergy.
an instance of an engine, vehicle, aircraft, or boat stalling.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: speed must be maintained to avoid a stall and loss of control
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Tốc độ phải được duy trì để tránh bị đình trệ và mất kiểm soát

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: (of a motor vehicle or its engine) stop running, typically because of an overload on the engine.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: her car stalled at the crossroads
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Xe của cô bị đình trệ ở ngã tư đường

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: stop or cause to stop making progress.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: his career had stalled, hers taken off
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: sự nghiệp của anh đã bị đình trệ, cô đã cất cánh

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: put or keep (an animal) in a stall, especially in order to fatten it.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: the horses were stalled at Upper Bolney Farm
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Những con ngựa bị đình trệ ở trang trại Upper Bolney
